  "prompt": "What are some good sources for free instrumental music to use in video tutorials?",
  "response": "Finding high-quality free instrumental music for video tutorials can greatly enhance the viewer's experience. Here are some excellent sources where you can find free instrumental music:\n\n### 1. **Free Music Archive (FMA)**\n   - **Website**: [freemusicarchive.org](https://freemusicarchive.org)\n   - **Description**: Offers a wide range of music genres, including instrumental tracks. Many are free to use under Creative Commons licenses.\n\n### 2. **Incompetech**\n   - **Website**: [incompetech.com](https://incompetech.com)\n   - **Description**: Created by Kevin MacLeod, this site offers a vast library of royalty-free instrumental music. You can use the music for free as long as you provide proper attribution.\n\n### 3. **Bensound**\n   - **Website**: [bensound.com](https://www.bensound.com)\n   - **Description**: Offers a selection of free instrumental music tracks. Free use requires attribution to the artist.\n\n### 4. **Musopen**\n   - **Website**: [musopen.org](https://musopen.org)\n   - **Description**: Focuses on classical music, with many public domain instrumental tracks that are free to use without attribution.\n\n### 5. **YouTube Audio Library**\n   - **Website**: [YouTube Audio Library](https://www.youtube.com/audiolibrary)\n   - **Description**: Offers a variety of free instrumental music tracks that are royalty-free and safe to use in your videos. No attribution is required for most tracks.\n\n### 6. **Jamendo**\n   - **Website**: [jamendo.com](https://www.jamendo.com)\n   - **Description**: Features a large collection of music from independent artists. Many tracks are available under Creative Commons licenses.\n\n### 7. **SoundCloud**\n   - **Website**: [soundcloud.com](https://soundcloud.com)\n   - **Description**: Use the search filters to find tracks labeled with Creative Commons licenses. Always check the specific license terms for each track.\n\n### 8. **ccMixter**\n   - **Website**: [ccmixter.org](http://ccmixter.org)\n   - **Description**: A community music site featuring tracks licensed under Creative Commons. Many instrumental tracks are available for free use.\n\n### 9. **FreePD**\n   - **Website**: [freepd.com](https://freepd.com)\n   - **Description**: Offers a collection of public domain music, including instrumental tracks that are completely free to use.\n\n### 10. **Pixabay Music**\n   - **Website**: [pixabay.com/music](https://pixabay.com/music)\n   - **Description**: Provides a variety of royalty-free instrumental tracks. No attribution is required.\n\n### Tips for Using Free Music:\n- **Always check the license**: Even if the music is free, there may be restrictions on how you can use it (e.g., attribution required, non-commercial use only).\n- **Provide proper attribution**: If the license requires it, make sure to credit the artist in your video description or credits.\n\nThese sources should provide you with plenty of options for finding the perfect instrumental music to accompany your video tutorials.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
